 East London - The Buffalo City Metro has started with the process of disinfecting its public areas and cleaning its streets. Executive Mayor Councillor Xola Pakati, who has set aside his Fridays to roll out his sleeves, led one of the three Citywide campaigns in East London on Friday morning. "As part of mitigating the Covid 19 virus, the City has identified a list of public areas that have huge traffic volumes of people, which carry the risk of spreading the virus," the Buffalo City Metro said. In East London, the Municipality sprayed and cleaned ebuhlanty, Gilwell Mall, Border taxi ranks and the CBD. "Meanwhile teams are also out in full force at the Mdantsane taxi ranks, Cambridge cemetry and Bhisho." The Municipality is taking advantage of the lockdown by intensifying its effort towards grass cutting, gutter clearing, weed picking, illegal dumps clearing, bush clearing. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 